activateAccount().details: Activate the caller's account by paying the activation fee

checkAirdropClaimed(address,address).details: Check if a user has claimed an airdrop

returns.hasClaimedAirdrop: Whether the user has claimed the airdrop

params.mintNFT: Whether to also mint an NFT

constructor.details: Constructor sets up the ecosystem contract

params._mintCost: Initial cost to mint an NFT (in wei)
params._trustScoreContract: Address of the TrustScore adapter contract

getReputationScore(address).details: Get the reputation score for an address

getUserDetails(address,address).details: Get a user's trust score details and NFT status

params.airdropAddress: Optional address of specific airdrop to check eligibility for

returns.eligibleForAirdrop: Whether user is eligible for specific airdrop (or general minimum if no address provided)
returns.hasClaimedAirdrop: Whether user has claimed the specific airdrop (always false if no address provided)
returns.isActivated: Whether the user's account is activated
returns.kycFilterLevel: User's KYC filter level for incoming transactions

isTransactionAllowed(address,address).details: Check if a transaction between two addresses would be allowed by KYC filters

returns.allowed: Whether the transaction would be allowed

mintTrustNFT().details: Mint a dynamic NFT that evolves with trust score

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

refreshNFTTrustScore(uint256).details: Allow a user to refresh their NFT's trust score

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. setKYCFilter(uint256).details: Set the KYC filter level for the caller

params.level: The KYC filter level to set

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

mintTrustNFT().notice: User must meet minimum trust score requirements
